Beijing natural ecology continues to attract more than 500 species of wildlife city “settlement” - Chinane.com
2020-07-26 05:03:17 Source: Beijing Youth Daily Author: Wang Sishuo Editor: Wang Sishuo
The capital's natural ecology continues to attract wildlife city “settlement”
More than 500 species of wildlife in Beijing
This newspaper (Reporter Wang Bin) The Beijing Youth Daily reporter learned from the Municipal Landscaping Bureau that in recent years as the natural ecological environment of the capital continues to improve, the species and number of wild animals have continued to increase.
At present, the number of terrestrial spine wildlife inhabited in Beijing has increased to more than 500 species, including brown horse chicken, black stork and other national protection animals at the national level, such as plaque, swan, gray crane and mandarin duck.
Whether it's a city forest in the second ring, or a tiny wetland embedded between buildings, not only brings nature to the capital's citizens, but also attracts wildlife to “settle” in the city.
In the middle of summer, Songshan National Nature Reserve is located in the Yanshan Mountains in the northwest of Yanqing District.
A raccoon plays leisurely beside the mountain stream, and two dog badgers beat each other.
Looking back, a wild boar can not help the body “thickling”, is rubbing the bark. By the end of 2019, the green sea with a total area of more than 6,200 hectares was living in 178 species of wild animals, including national conservation gold carving and national secondary protection animal spoon chicken, plaque, nearly one-third of the city's wildlife,” said Hu Qiaoli, director of Songshan National Nature Reserve Management Office All kinds can see traces here.
“In Matsuyama, wildlife is the real 'owner', and our staff can only be the bodyguard at best.”
Hu Qiaoli said that in order to understand the wildlife situation in the protected area, more than 30 professional patrols every day patrol along 16 carefully crafted protection routes, and there will be a “big circle” every month, taking a whole day to almost the entire reserve.
“During the inspection, not only to check the recording of biodiversity, but also the installation of artificial bird nests, rescue injured wildlife, installation of field infrared cameras, and so on.”
More than 200 infrared cameras have been installed in the Songshan National Nature Reserve to record the living conditions of wildlife in the forest.
Hu Qiaoli explained that with the abundance of biodiversity in the reserve over the years, more and more wild animals appear in the camera, leopard cats, raccoons and pig badgers have become “resident guests”, and the “mirror rate” of national secondary protection animal springaurus is getting higher and higher.
Zhang Zhiming, Director of Wildlife and Wetland Conservation Department of Beijing Municipal Bureau of Landscaping Bureau, said that Beijing's terrestrial spine wildlife has increased from 461 species in 1994 to more than 500 species now.
The growing number of wildlife in cities is closely related to the upgrading of urban greenery in the capital in recent years.
In particular, the new round of millionacre afforestation, which began in 2018, proposes to reinvent the urban ecological environment, enhance the ecological function of woodland greenery and highlight the concept of “near-nature”.
Planning aims to interconnect with the surrounding green areas, facilitate wildlife “visit friends and family”, planted trees are also animal favorite honey, food plants.
Black Land “Seed” Out of Agriculture Modernization - Xinhuan.com
Xinhua News Agency, Harbin, July 26th Telegram: Black Land “Seed” Out of Agriculture Modernization
In the midsummer, two spraying agent aircraft from the second operation station of Friendship Farm Fifth Management Zone 2 mu high-yielding demonstration fields, forming two white lines, green fields with black rice seedlings out of the “world first” several big characters are particularly striking.
Kong Lingqiang, the station director of the station, said that this aircraft can spray agents on more than 6,000 acres of arable land a day, about 8 times more efficient than drones, hundreds of times the manual.
This farm is located in the territory of Youyi County, Heilongjiang Province, China's first grain-producing province. From the sound of cut rice in the past to the motor sound of today, the traditional Chinese farming and farm transform on this black soil belt.
In addition to aircraft, satellites are also used in the modern agricultural production of Friendship Farms.
Kong Lingqiang explained that, on the one hand, they use satellite remote sensing technology to achieve accurate fertilization, reduce agricultural inputs and reduce pollution. On the other hand, satellite navigation technology can improve the level of standardization of farm machinery field operations.
During this year's rice production, the farm expanded the operating area of satellite-based unmanned rice transplanting technology from 3,000 acres last year to 30,000 acres.
This technology makes seedlings more uniform, maximizes the use of sunlight and arable land resources, and saves 16 yuan of labor costs per mu.
The farm tried new technologies such as informatization and intelligence in agricultural production, forming the largest agricultural machinery group in China from the ground to the sky.
According to statistics, the total farm farm ownership capacity of 49,000 units (pieces), field comprehensive mechanization rate of 99.8%.
Agricultural machinery operation to achieve GPS satellite navigation 100%, dry field precision seeding 100%, dry field horsepower Locomotive operation 100%.
“Green agriculture, smart agriculture, digital agriculture are the way to modernize agriculture.”
Friendship Farm Director Liu Hua-lian said.
The key to modernization of agriculture lies in scientific and technological progress.
Agricultural reclamation in Heilongjiang, represented by farms, has played a leading role in modern large agriculture “aircraft carrier” demonstration and leading role, initially establishing a modern agricultural industrial system led by large-scale planting, standardized production and industrialization management.
On the outskirts of Youyi County, there is an area of 350,000 square meters of agricultural machinery exhibition park.
Here, more than 140 (pieces) agricultural tools have been introduced and used in Heilongjiang agricultural reclamation over the years.
These agricultural tools and farms witness the modernization of our country's agricultural development.
