Researchers found that an enzyme in platelets accelerates platelet coagulation before a heart attack or stroke attack.
As a result, they developed a drug that temporarily inhibits platelet coagulation, avoiding blood vessel clogging and preventing heart disease and stroke.
Researchers say the drug inhibits the coagulant effect of platelets only when signs of heart disease or stroke appear.
