Before volunteering to fill out, understand what is a professional grade difference - China.com
2020-07-27 02:22:36 Source: Chongqing Morning News Author: Yu Xiao Responsibility Editor: Yu Xiao
Before volunteering to do so, understand what is a professional grade difference
Every year, students or parents are not aware of the terminology involved in the voluntary application, and thus affect the voluntary filing.
This year, five universities from Beijing Jiaotong University, Beijing University of Science and Technology, Beijing University of Posts and Telecommunications, Beijing Forestry University and Beijing University of Chemical Technology jointly issued 2020 admissions policy, eliminating professional grade difference.
What does professional-grade difference mean, and what is the significance of volunteering?
There are three ways to assign professional rules
Experts remind that before filing a volunteer, be sure to read the “Admissions Charter” of your favorite schools, to understand the admission rules of colleges, including regulation ratio, professional allocation rules, etc.
Professional allocation rules, refers to the university after the profile, for professional admission are mainly professional priority, score priority, professional grade difference three ways.
The specific method used by universities will be specified in the Admissions Charter.
But there are also some universities where the principle of admission is the total score priority, there is no grade difference between majors.
That is to say, candidates within the admission range are queued according to the total score, when the score does not reach the first professional volunteer, then see if the second professional volunteer has reached the second professional volunteer, and so on until admission to the last professional volunteer, there is no grade difference between each professional volunteer.
The so-called “professional grade difference” is that when an institution arranges a candidate's profession, according to one or more points published in the admissions charter, to determine the admissions of volunteer candidates from different specialties. This score value is “professional grade difference”.
That is, the difference between the scores of students enrolled in the first professional volunteer and non-first professional volunteers, such as 3 points, 2 points, 1 point, etc.
For example.
Assuming that students are enrolled in college A, 560 points, their professional volunteering are: computer, international trade, automation, mechanical engineering, e-commerce, professional admissions of A colleges to implement professional grade difference, grade difference is 2 points, 1 point, 1 point, 0 points.
In professional assignment, if Xiaoming's first professional volunteer meets the professional admission requirements and the professional planned balance, then Xiaoming is admitted to the “computer” professional; if the computer is not accepted, his score will be subtracted by 2 points, according to the score of 558 as the first professional volunteer for “International Trade” Easy” sorting candidates to determine whether they meet the criteria for professional admission; if still not, score minus 1 point ( (557 points) for the third professional volunteer “automated” admission; if still not met, the score is subtracted by 1 point (i.e. 556 points) for admission to the fourth profession, the subsequent profession will not be reduced if it still fails to meet its professional volunteer, and so on.
Different college professional level difference set
With the popularity of parallel volunteerism, many universities have now abolished professional grade difference, but some universities still retain this method this year. Judging from the “Admissions Charter” published by each school, this year, mainly over 20 universities have set professional grade difference.
For example, Sichuan Agricultural University, Shandong University of Science and Technology, Heilongjiang University of Traditional Chinese Medicine, Jiangsu University of Science and Technology, Jiangxi Normal University, Chengdu Medical College, Northeast Electric Power University, Jimei University, Nanjing Medical University, Nanjing University of Technology, Ningxia University, Shandong University of Technology, China Civil Aviation Flight College, etc.
In each of these universities, each university has a different level of specialization.
Some universities have grade differences in every major. For example, Ningxia University, the files of candidates who have been put to the school, decreasing one point in order according to the order in which candidates are enrolled in the professional volunteer order.
Some universities set different professional grade differences between different disciplines.
For example, Jimei University, professional volunteer level difference is 4 points, that is, the first professional volunteer and other professional volunteer level difference is 3 points, no difference between other professional volunteers, is considered parallel volunteer, and the difference between other professional volunteers and the spin-off professional level is 1 point.
When filing a volunteer, candidates and parents must carefully read the admission policy of the reported school to see if there is a professional grade difference, what the form of the grade difference is, while fully considering the score, also have a reasonable analysis of the proposed school and profession, if the institution explicitly adopts a fractional difference in the admissions charter For admission, when choosing a profession, pay attention to the gradient between the major, improve the chances of admission.
